definitions.definition: The act or process of becoming manifest .
examples: The last known manifestation of the ghost was over ten years ago.

definitions.definition: The embodiment of an intangible , or variable thing.
examples: This particular manifestation resembled a young girl crying.

definitions.definition: The symptoms or observable conditions which are seen as a result of some disease .
A pattern or logo on a sheet of glass, as decoration or to prevent people from accidentally walking into it.
Willing something into existence (see manifest ( verb ) ).
